summary:
Yo, friends! To anyone with Sun, Moon, Ultra Sun, or Ultra Moon, I have no one to trade with!
I have some recently hatched babes...
body:
Giving away some Pokemon!

Yo, friends! To anyone with Sun, Moon, Ultra Sun, or Ultra Moon, I have no one to trade with!

I have some recently hatched babes right here! Three Chimchars, two Torchics, an Oshawott, two Trapinches (they eventually evolve into Flygon), two Dhelmise, four Scatterbugs (eventually evolve into Vivillons) and four Vivillon (the purple isn’t for trade unless you can convince me otherwise).

These aren’t amazingly rare catches or anything… So I won’t ask for anything too special. I’m just trying to fill out my pokedex and I’m a littlw too lazy to catch some things. Let me know if you’re interested in trading for any of these little babs!! It’s first come, first served and you can ask for more than one pokemon!

I look forward to hearing from you~!

summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1428: Porygon-Z (Triumphant)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1428: Porygon-Z (Triumphant)
body:
Porygon-Z cards were always a little bit different. There was some sort of quirk that was meant to show its nature as a Pokemon with computer code that wasn’t quite right. This card did not disappoint when it came to flavor, even bringing a letter from the Greek Alphabet into its attack name. The effects were strange to match. Was strange enough to be good? No, not always, but it did mean that it had an interesting twist.

110 HP was pretty low for a Stage 2 by this point. There were plenty reaching 130 and 140, so this was pretty sad. It was low enough to be picked off by Zekrom and Reshiram, and even Gyarados with an Expert Belt could hit hard enough if at full power. The x2 Fighting Weakness added Donphan, Machamp, and Terrakion to that list. Needless to say, Porygon-Z was pretty frail in a lot of important situations. The Retreat Cost here was 2. Some help was nice if you could fit it, though Double Colorless Energy being available made things a bit easier.

Dimension Transfer was support, but sadly was also flip-based. Once during your turn, you could flip a coin. If heads, you searched your discard pile for a Trainer card and put it on top of your deck. And yes, it was prevented if Porygon-Z was affected by a Special Condition. This was typical of Poke-Powers, but it’s important to mention it here due to Porygon-Z’s attack. Anyway, it was really nice to get an extra use out of a good Supporter when this worked. Too bad about it being ridiculously unreliable. This was best thought of as a nice bonus more than the draw to the card.

Suspicious Beam β was… odd. 80 damage for 3 Colorless Energy was workable. Double Colorless Energy could speed it up, and while it wasn’t the most powerful thing out there, it would be taking Prizes off most things within 2 attacks. Oh, but there was a drawback, something other attackers with this sort of damage didn’t have to deal with. If Porygon-Z didn’t have any Rainbow Energy attached to it, it did 20 damage to itself and was also Confused. There’s the bad coding part of the flavor, and in this case, it made Porygon-Z inferior to other Colorless Pokemon such as Garchomp C LV.X and Tornadus. Needing that specific Special Energy was a lot to ask.

Porygon-Z was a card that was pretty close to being good, since its attack was decent when the needs were fulfilled while providing nice support when flips were good. But flips weren’t always good, and relying on getting the right Special Energy at the time, especially when you also wanted to use Double Colorless Energy alongside it, brought too much variance. It was a fun card to look at, but it just didn’t play very well in practice.

  • You will receive a full resolution file of your commission, if you post this to your own accounts you must credit back to me. 
  • Any commissions may be used as examples as up above, if that is an issue, let me know in our emails. 

Will Do:

Animals and Creatures, Original characters, Fanart, Monsters/demons/human hybrids, Couples (any type!), Non-sexual Nudity, Anthros/Furries, light gore or candy gore, Pet Portraits/Design Your Pet as an OC

Will Not Do:

NSFW porn/fetish, Cars, Mecha

Thanks everyone! I may do some marker commissions in the future.
